**[01/2026]** Joined [NVIDIA Cosmos Lab](https://research.nvidia.com/labs/cosmos-lab/) as a Staff Research Scientist, working on world foundation models for Physical AI.
**[04/2025]** [MANZANO](https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.16197) is accepted to ICLR 2026. A simple and scalable unified multimodal model with a hybrid vision tokenizer.
**[01/2025]** [Cosmos World Foundation Model Platform](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.03575) is released — a comprehensive platform for building world foundation models.
**[10/2024]** Three papers accepted to ICLR 2025: [MM1.5](https://arxiv.org/abs/2409.20566), [MM-Ego](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.07177), and [Ferret-UI 2](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.18967).
**[07/2024]** Two papers accepted to ECCV 2024: [MM1](https://arxiv.org/abs/2403.09611) and [Ferret-UI](https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.05719).
**[04/2024]** [Ferret-v2](https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.07973) is accepted to COLM 2024. An improved baseline for referring and grounding with LLMs.
**[03/2024]** We release the checkpoints [here](https://github.com/apple/ml-veclip) for [veCLIP](https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.07699), which achieves 83.07% on IN1K zero-shot.
**[02/2024]** [Ferret](https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.07704) is accepted to ICLR 2024 as Spotlight (5% Acceptance Rate).
**[10/2022]** Selected as one of the Young Scholar Award recipients for NeurIPS 2022.
**[09/2022]** One paper accepted to NeurIPS 2022: [GLIPv2](https://arxiv.org/abs/2206.05836). A team effort to push [CVinW](https://computer-vision-in-the-wild.github.io/eccv-2022/).
**[09/2022]** Organizing ECCV Workshop [*Computer Vision in the Wild (CVinW)*](https://computer-vision-in-the-wild.github.io/eccv-2022/), where two challenges [*ICinW*](https://eval.ai/web/challenges/challenge-page/1832/overview) and [*ODinW*](https://eval.ai/web/challenges/challenge-page/1839/overview) are hosted.
**[03/2022]** One paper accepted to CVPR 2022: [GLIP](https://arxiv.org/abs/2112.03857) as an Oral & Best Paper Finalist.
